\# Day 1 – Cloud \& AWS Fundamentals



\## What is Cloud Computing?

Cloud Computing is the on-demand delivery of Computing resources (servers,storage,databases,networking,software) over the internet with pay as you use pricing.



\## Why AWS?

Cost - Pay as you go
Scaling - Instant
Maintenance - AWS manages
Reliability - Highly available
Global presence,high Availability,security and compliance , Mature data ecosystem, Market leader


\## Cloud Service Models

\- IaaS (Infrastructure as a Service) 
	- you manage - OS ,applications
	- AWS manages : hardware
	- Example - EC2

\- PaaS (Platform as a service)
	- You manage - Application logic
	- AWS manages: OS, runtime
	- Example: RDS

\- SaaS (Software as a service)
	- you use the software
	- Example: Gmail, Salesforce


\## AWS Global Infrastructure

\- Region - Mumbai

\- Availability Zone -  Independent data centers within a region, used for high Availability



